[normal]There is nothing educational about the creation of academies and the inevitable chains that follow. 
[normal]They seem only to serve the interests of private industry. Motivated by money, or power, or winning league tables
[normal],
[normal] they have lost the original intention of education [from the Latin 
[normal]educere
[normal], to lead out], which is to consider the individual child, and his or her needs. 
