[normal]It is an irony that 
[normal]the very process which was publicly heralded as intended as 
[normal]curing the so-called failing schools has so much damage. Advice from teaching unions and other professionals was of
[normal]fered and ignored. The private sector was itching to get its hands on education, and the government was itching to appease big business.
